Tere naam se jeene ki
Tere naam se marne ki

Dil maang raha hai mohalat
Tere saath dhadakne ki
Tere naam se jeene ki
Tere naam se marne ki

So guys we went to Malviya Nagar and found these very old couple working hard to earn a living, when I went there and saw them struggling, I couldn't stop but cried. They said they start early at 6.30 am and by 1.30 am they could only earn Rs 60/-, so went ahead and bought all thier stuff for a day. Thank you so much smile karne aur ham koshish karenge ki apko hamesha hasate rahe aur agar apka mann kare toh ye hasi dusre ko bhi spread kar denaa, video SHARE kar dena.

snippet.title: Baba Ka Dhaba News: After Viral Video, Help Pours In For Delhi Couple Running Baba Ka Dhaba
snippet.description:
Baba Ka Dhaba Video: The power of social media has now led to help pouring in for an elderly couple selling home-cooked meals from a tiny stand in south Delhi's Malviya Nagar. A video of the couple who runs a food joint called "Baba Ka Dhaba" has been widely shared on social media. In the video shot by blogger Gaurav Vasan yesterday, 80-year-old Kanta Prasad shared that he and his wife Badami Devi start cooking at 6.30 am and are ready with the day's meal by 9.30 am. Dal, curry, parathas and rice were kept in large dishes, ready to serve for around Rs 30-50 a plate. Today, a constant stream of customers was seen at the eatery.  "We are very happy with the number of customers that are turning up now. We are grateful for the public support," Kanta Prasad told NDTV.  "When I came here yesterday, I had goosebumps listening to their plight," Mr Vasan, who shot the video, said.

snippet.title: EVERY DAY IMPOSTOR LIFE - AMONG US ANIMATION
snippet.description:
This time we want to show you how a impostor rejects to continue this way, and wants to help the crew, but at a certain moments the other members notice is a impostor, if he is good now, how can resolve this situation?
Thanks you so much for support me! 
I love you! ‚ù§Ô∏è

Original Animation by Hornstromp.

Among Us is an American made science fiction based murder mystery video game developed and published by Innersloth. Inc. It was released for IOS and Android on June 15, 2018, for PC on Steam on August 18, 2018 and for Dajolg on November 2, 2018. Among Us follows a crew being picked off one by one by an impostor.

In each game the player is one of 4 to 10 living and working in several different environments. One of these crewmates is an Impostor whose main goal is to kill everyone else. The remainder of the players are part of the regular crew who are just trying to escape unharmed. To do this, they have to complete several tasks or (better yet) find the Impostor and vote them out Survivor-style. If they are successful, the Crew wins. If the Impostor manages to kill them all, the player is victorious. In a 10 player game with one Impostor, there is a 10% chance of being an Impostor.

The free map, Skeld, has 14 different rooms that are connected by 7 hallways. Everyone begins the game in the Cafeteria and, depending on the host's settings, as well as on RNG, Crew members have to visit some or most of the other rooms to complete their tasks.

While Impostors do not have tasks as their specific objectives, they can fake ‚Äúcompleting‚Äù certain activities as a way to gain everyone else's trust. Every user has a chance to call an emergency meeting or, upon seeing a dead body, to report it to everyone else. For the mobile release, discussions are only possible during these time-limited events.

If you are an Impostor, your main goal is to convince others that you are not the Impostor, while the Crew's job is to spot you out. Since it is a voting system where the person with the most votes gets eliminated from the game, it does not really matter who does what. Instead, your argumentative powers are what makes a difference. To sway people in one direction or another, you have to be prepared to make your case as convincing as possible. There is a short time-limit, so you either have to present very strong evidence or come up with a believable narrative that will take others off your trail.

When you are killed by the Impostor, you become a ghost. Although you cannot interact or discuss with others, you can help them complete tasks.

Streamers complained about chat being main form of communications, so a lot of streamers used discord for voice chat.

#AmongUs #AmongUsMeme
#AmongUsAnimation

snippet.title: I Tested Clickbait DIY Soap "Hacks"
snippet.description:
Hello friends! So, after a long break from testing out & reviewing clickbait hack videos (I think the photo and video hacks broke me), we decided to make a comeback into the genre by testing out these viral clickbait soap hacks that lots of hackers seem to love making - from Blossom to 5-Minute Crafts to Craft Factory and back. And you know me, I can't resist me some nice soap :). We tried a cloud soap hack, a gummy bear soap hack, and a cinnamon roll soap hack, and shenanigans ensued. 

What do you guys think of these soap hacks??

Also, a heads up - though we mention it in the video - cinnamon can be dangerous to use on your skin and ivory soap can release fumes when being microwaved (I guess that's why it smelled so bad), so definitely be careful if you take on any of these soap art "hacks" yourself!!

You can check out Katie from Royalty Soap's video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-UDhSQYVWss
You can check out the Blossom video that contains our hacks here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4I1tMz-VMtg
And you can check out Jenna's soap hand video here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fo3HwJNgi9M

This video is NOT sponsored!!

Safiya's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/safiyany/

MUSIC
Via AudioNetwork

snippet.title: What Fans Didn't Know About Eddie Van Halen
snippet.description:
The electric guitar is the definitive instrument of rock 'n' roll, and Eddie Van Halen is one of the few players who can claim to be among the greatest of all time. This is the untold truth of Eddie Van Halen.

Van Halen was the biggest hard rock band since KISS. According to Edward Van Halen: A Definitive Biography, KISS co-leader Gene Simmons was scouting talent for Casablanca Records in 1976 when he discovered Van Halen playing a show in West Hollywood. Simmons liked the group and booked them some studio time to record demos of 12 songs, and then flew the guys to New York City for overdubs at Jimi Hendrix's Electric Lady Studios and to play at a showcase for KISS' manager, Bill Aucoin. He declined to take on Van Halen as clients, but after the band returned to California, Simmons recruited Eddie Van Halen and his brother, drummer Alex Van Halen, to demo songs for the next KISS album, Love Gun. When KISS' actual guitarist Ace Frehley was tasked with recording the song "Christine Sixteen," his solo was a note-by-note re-creation of Eddie Van Halen's attempt.

A few years later, around 1982, Eddie was so tired of clashing with singer David Lee Roth that he attempted to join KISS, who were then in the process of splitting with guitarist Ace Frehley. Simmons told Guitar World: 

"Eddie said, 'I want to join KISS. I don't want to fight anymore with Roth.' I told him, 'Eddie, there's not enough room. You need to be in a band where you can direct the music.'" Watch the video to learn What Fans Didn't Know About Eddie Van Halen.

#EddieVanHalen

snippet.description:
The future of The Belt has begun as Marco Inaros wages Armageddon against the Inners for a lifetime of oppression and injustice.

¬ª Watch the new season of The Expanse now exclusively with your Prime Membership: http://bit.ly/TheExpanseAPV
¬ª SUBSCRIBE: http://bit.ly/PrimeVideoSubscribe

About The Expanse:
The disappearance of rich-girl-turned-political-activist Julie Mao links the lives of Ceres detective Joe Miller (Thomas Jane), accidental ship captain James Holden (Steven Strait) and U.N. politician Chrisjen Avasarala (Shohreh Aghdashloo). Amidst political tension between Earth, Mars and the Belt, they unravel the single greatest conspiracy of all time.

About The Expanse Seasons 2:
In this noir thriller set two hundred years in the future, the case of a missing young woman leads a washed-up detective across the solar system to uncover the greatest conspiracy in human history.

About The Expanse Seasons 3:
As the Rocinante crew digs deeper into the search for Prax's missing daughter, the war between Earth and Mars turns deadly in ways the solar system has never seen. But a new threat in the outer reaches of the Belt could prove much more dangerous, threatening to test the very future of humanity.

About The Expanse Seasons 4:
Season 4 of The Expanse, its first as a global Amazon Original, begins a new chapter for the series with the crew of the Rocinante on a mission from the U.N. to explore new worlds beyond the Ring Gate. Humanity has been given access to thousands of Earth-like planets which has created a land rush and furthered tensions between the opposing nations of Earth, Mars and the Belt. Ilus is the first of these planets, one rich with natural resources but also marked by the ruins of a long dead alien civilization. While Earthers, Martians and Belters maneuver to colonize Ilus and its natural resources, these early explorers don‚Äôt understand this new world and are unaware of the larger dangers that await them.

snippet.title: Eddie Van Halen: How The Guitarist Gave Michael Jackson A Big Hit With 'Beat It' On 'Thriller'
snippet.description:
Sign up for our Rock Newsletter here: https://bit.ly/3fjldAi
‚¨áÔ∏è Rock merch I'm loving right now:

Nirvana poster: https://amzn.to/3fmUMKc
Van Halen mini collectable guitar: https://amzn.to/3ebm1WM
Alice in Chains on MTV Unplugged: https://amzn.to/3ei0Hif
*I recieve a small commission from link purchases*

Today we discuss the collaboration of guitarist Eddie Van Halen and Michael Jackson on the song 'Beat It' from Jackson's album 'Thriller' which came out in 1982. RIP Eddie Van Halen

LOVE ROCK N‚Äô ROLL TRUE STORIES? NEVER MISS A BEAT 
FACEBOOK: @RNRTrueStories
TWITTER: @rocktruestories
BLOG: www.rockandrolltruestories.com

#vanhalen #michaeljackson #eddievanhalen #evh

What‚Äôs going on my fellow rock n‚Äô rollers. Don‚Äôt foget to hit the bell notification i con to be notified everytime i pout out a new video on my channel. Guitarist Eddie Van Halen would play a crucial role in pop star Michael Jackson‚Äôs hit song Beat it from his 6th album Thriller. The guitarist was taken by surprise when Thriller came out in 1982 and his name was nowhere to be found. Not only that but Eddie wasn‚Äôt the original guitarist who was asked to play on the song So what happened. Stay tuned to find out the full story.
The Who's Pete Townshend would claim that he was originally asked to play on the song Beat It, but was unable to and instead recommended Eddie Van Halen telling Rolling Stone
‚ÄúI was once asked by Michael Jackson to play electric guitar on the Thriller album,‚Äù ‚ÄúI said I couldn‚Äôt do it but recommended Eddie who called and we chatted. He was utterly charming, happy about the connection, but told me how much he was enjoying playing keyboards. His smile was just classic. A man in his rightful place, so happy to be doing what he did.‚Äù
Eddie Van Halen was personally asked by Thriller‚Äôs producer Quincy Jones to help with the song. Eddie admitted in a 2012 interview with CNN that he didn‚Äôt know a person named Quincy at the time and thought the phone call was a practical joke saying:
‚ÄúI went off on him. I went, ‚ÄòWhat do you want, you f-ing so-and-so!,‚Äô‚Äù ‚ÄúAnd he goes, ‚ÄòIs this Eddie?‚Äô I said, ‚ÄòYeah, what the hell do you want?‚Äô ‚ÄòThis is Quincy.‚Äô I‚Äôm thinking to myself, ‚ÄòI don‚Äôt know anyone named Quincy.‚Äô He goes, ‚ÄòQuincy Jones, man.‚Äô I went, ‚ÄòOhhh, sorry!‚Äô‚Äù Eddie agreed to do the track but was also skeptical about how much he had in common with Jackson considering they played different styes of music. But Jackson had actually written ‚ÄúBeat It‚Äù to be a rock song, helped in large part Toto guitarist Steve Lukather who also played on the track. 
Van Halen had a break in their working schedule and according to the guitarist he did the session for free and it only took about 20 minutes and his part amounted to about 20 seconds guitar solo on the track,. Quincy Jones wanted the guitarist to improvise recalling in a BBC documentary about Jackson 
"I'm not gonna sit here and try to tell you what to play.
"The reason you are here is because of what you do play."
Eddie would play the solo and according to engineers in the studio it was during that session that one of the speakers caught on fire. One of the engineers would exclaim ‚Äúthis must be really good.‚Äù
Right before Eddie‚Äôs guitar solo begins, a noise is heard that sounds like somebody knocking at a door. It was originally reported that the knock was a person walking into Eddie's recording studio. A different  story claimed that the sound was simply the musician knocking on his own guitar.[] The sound, however, is that of Jackson knocking on a drum case, as he is credited in the album's liner notes.
Eddie would tell CNN he listened to the track and re-arranged the entire track while Jackson was out of the studio, but the popstar had no issue with the song‚Äôs new arrangement as he said here. 
Eddie would also claim in the same interview that Jackson‚Äôs band was very insular and that they rarely asked for outside help from musicians on records. Eddie was not credited on the album, he didnt get paid and he wasn‚Äôt in the music video, but he did make several live appearances with Jackson.. In fact Eddie would tell Piers Morgan in 2012 he was naive about how popular Jackson was saying in 2012 ‚Äúwhose gonna know if i play on this black kid‚Äôs record?‚Äù Eddie was probably right to be a little naive considering this was 1982 and MTV wasn‚Äôt playing a lot of black artists, in fact I‚Äôll be doing another story in the future about how playing Michael Jackson became a huge fight for MTV and how the king of pop literally saved the network, but that‚Äôs a story for another time. 
Following the release of Thriller Eddie recalled being at Tower Records and hearing the song playing in the store and how some people were critical of his guitar playing on the track claiming. "The solo comes on, and I hear these kids in front of me going, 'Listen to this guy trying to sound like Eddie Van Halen.' I tapped him on the shoulder and said, 'That is me!' That was hilarious."

Sign up for our Rock Newsletter here: https://bit.ly/3fjldAi
‚¨áÔ∏è Rock merch I'm loving right now:

Nirvana poster: https://amzn.to/3fmUMKc
Van Halen mini collectable guitar: https://amzn.to/3ebm1WM
Alice in Chains on MTV Unplugged: https://amzn.to/3ei0Hif
*I recieve a small commission from link purchases*

Today we discuss the collaboration of guitarist Eddie Van Halen and Michael Jackson on the song 'Beat It' from Jackson's album 'Thriller' which came out in 1982. 

LOVE ROCK N‚Äô ROLL TRUE STORIES? NEVER MISS A BEAT 
FACEBOOK: @RNRTrueStories
TWITTER: @rocktruestories
BLOG: www.rockandrolltruestories.com

#vanhalen #michaeljackson #eddievanhalen #evh

What‚Äôs going on my fellow rock n‚Äô rollers. Don‚Äôt foget to hit the bell notification i con to be notified everytime i pout out a new video on my channel. Guitarist Eddie Van Halen would play a crucial role in pop star Michael Jackson‚Äôs hit song Beat it from his 6th album Thriller. The guitarist was taken by surprise when Thriller came out in 1982 and his name was nowhere to be found. Not only that but Eddie wasn‚Äôt the original guitarist who was asked to play on the song So what happened. Stay tuned to find out the full story.
The Who's Pete Townshend would claim that he was originally asked to play on the song Beat It, but was unable to and instead recommended Eddie Van Halen telling Rolling Stone
‚ÄúI was once asked by Michael Jackson to play electric guitar on the Thriller album,‚Äù ‚ÄúI said I couldn‚Äôt do it but recommended Eddie who called and we chatted. He was utterly charming, happy about the connection, but told me how much he was enjoying playing keyboards. His smile was just classic. A man in his rightful place, so happy to be doing what he did.‚Äù
Eddie Van Halen was personally asked by Thriller‚Äôs producer Quincy Jones to help with the song. Eddie admitted in a 2012 interview with CNN that he didn‚Äôt know a person named Quincy at the time and thought the phone call was a practical joke saying:
‚ÄúI went off on him. I went, ‚ÄòWhat do you want, you f-ing so-and-so!,‚Äô‚Äù ‚ÄúAnd he goes, ‚ÄòIs this Eddie?‚Äô I said, ‚ÄòYeah, what the hell do you want?‚Äô ‚ÄòThis is Quincy.‚Äô I‚Äôm thinking to myself, ‚ÄòI don‚Äôt know anyone named Quincy.‚Äô He goes, ‚ÄòQuincy Jones, man.‚Äô I went, ‚ÄòOhhh, sorry!‚Äô‚Äù Eddie agreed to do the track but was also skeptical about how much he had in common with Jackson considering they played different styes of music. But Jackson had actually written ‚ÄúBeat It‚Äù to be a rock song, helped in large part Toto guitarist Steve Lukather who also played on the track. 
Van Halen had a break in their working schedule and according to the guitarist he did the session for free and it only took about 20 minutes and his part amounted to about 20 seconds guitar solo on the track,. Quincy Jones wanted the guitarist to improvise recalling in a BBC documentary about Jackson 
"I'm not gonna sit here and try to tell you what to play.
"The reason you are here is because of what you do play."
Eddie would play the solo and according to engineers in the studio it was during that session that one of the speakers caught on fire. One of the engineers would exclaim ‚Äúthis must be really good.‚Äù
Right before Eddie‚Äôs guitar solo begins, a noise is heard that sounds like somebody knocking at a door. It was originally reported that the knock was a person walking into Eddie's recording studio. A different  story claimed that the sound was simply the musician knocking on his own guitar.[] The sound, however, is that of Jackson knocking on a drum case, as he is credited in the album's liner notes.
Eddie would tell CNN he listened to the track and re-arranged the entire track while Jackson was out of the studio, but the popstar had no issue with the song‚Äôs new arrangement as he said here. 
Eddie would also claim in the same interview that Jackson‚Äôs band was very insular and that they rarely asked for outside help from musicians on records. Eddie was not credited on the album, he didnt get paid and he wasn‚Äôt in the music video, but he did make several live appearances with Jackson.. In fact Eddie would tell Piers Morgan in 2012 he was naive about how popular Jackson was saying in 2012 ‚Äúwhose gonna know if i play on this black kid‚Äôs record?‚Äù Eddie was probably right to be a little naive considering this was 1982 and MTV wasn‚Äôt playing a lot of black artists, in fact I‚Äôll be doing another story in the future about how playing Michael Jackson became a huge fight for MTV and how the king of pop literally saved the network, but that‚Äôs a story for another time. 
Following the release of Thriller Eddie recalled being at Tower Records and hearing the song playing in the store and how some people were critical of his guitar playing on the track claiming. "The solo comes on, and I hear these kids in front of me going, 'Listen to this guy trying to sound like Eddie Van Halen.' I tapped him on the shoulder and said, 'That is me!' That was hilarious."

snippet.title: The Sad Death Of Eddie Van Halen
snippet.description:
The rock 'n' roll world took a hit today, as it said goodbye to one of the most influential guitarists of the 20th century. TMZ reported that Eddie Van Halen, of his riotously successful namesake band, lost his years-long battle with throat cancer. He was just 65-years-old. His wife Janie, son Wolfgang, and brother Alex were with him when he died. Eddie had been struggling to fight the cancer for over a decade, but he finally succumbed to it after it recently spread to his brain and other organs. Eddie himself attributed the disease not to his years of heavy smoking, but to a metal guitar pick that he used to bite down on over two decades ago.

Eddie and Alex founded their eponymous band in Pasadena, California with bassist Michael Anthony and singer David Lee Roth in 1972. The band released more than 10 albums, many of which enjoyed multi-platinum sales.

A bandmate as well as a son, Wolfgang Van Halen actually had an excellent relationship with his father. He joined the band as bassist in 2006, going on tour and releasing the studio album A Different Kind of Truth with his dad in 2012. Wolfgang lamented the loss of his father on Twitter not long after his passing.

"I can't believe I'm having to write this, but my father, Edward Lodewijk Van Halen, has lost his long and arduous battle with cancer this morning. He was the best father I could ever ask for. Every moment I've shared with him on and off stage was a gift... I love you so much, Pop."

Alice In Chains guitarist and co-lead vocalist William Duval also said goodbye to his friend Eddie on Twitter:

"Unbelievable. Hard to imagine a world without you in it. So many treasured memories attached to your music, your sound, your image, your attitude."

No doubt the memories and mourning will continue to lament the sad death of Eddie Van Halen in the coming days.

#EddieVanHalen #VanHalen

Read full article: https://www.grunge.com/257519/the-sad-death-of-eddie-van-halen/

snippet.title: Dutchavelli - Cool With Me (feat. M1llionz)
snippet.description:
The official video for Dutchavelli - Cool With Me (feat. M1llionz)

Stream 'Cool With Me' now: https://dutchavelli.lnk.to/CoolWithMe

Subscribe to the Dutchavelli channel for all the best and latest official music videos, behind the scenes and live performances:
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCz73pXXitXqx8NxGXAkij7w?sub_confirmation=1

See more official videos from Dutchavelli here:
https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLGzI6D0SY8BeKNPlGzjQcR_vzSSnFOrYg

Follow Dutchavelli:
Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/dutchavelli/
Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/dutchavellimusic
Twitter - https://twitter.com/dutchavelli1

Make no mistake ‚Äì Dutchavelli is doing it for greatness. The east London rapper set a goal four years ago ‚Äì to be the best. A rapper‚Äôs rapper with true global appeal, a handsome side road hustler gone national, a man with a firm presence and a clear vision ‚Äì Dutch has it all. And ‚Äì in ‚ÄúOnly If You Knew‚Äù and ‚ÄúSurely‚Äù, both featured on the GRM Daily channel ‚Äì he already has two smashes under his belt...

Dutch‚Äôs influences include heavy duty rap legends like Tupac and Eminem ‚Äì ‚ÄúI used to know them songs off the top of my head. I would take pride in knowing them off the back of my head.‚Äù ‚Äì and devoured US battle rap videos and the UK‚Äôs own ‚ÄòLord Of The Mics‚Äô series.

The music Dutch makes today is a lyrically dense take on classic UK rap genres. But one that‚Äôs been arrived at via the smoked-out, hook heavy US sounds of Pop Smoke and Future and blasted into action by Dutch‚Äôs inimitable voice. It‚Äôs drill 2.0, if you will. Or Next Gen Road Rap. Whatever. The main thing is ‚Äì Dutch can rap. You can call it what you want. 

#Dutchavelli #CoolWithMe #M1llionz

snippet.title: The Expanse ‚Äì Season 5 Official Trailer
snippet.description:
The future of The Belt has begun as Marco Inaros wages Armageddon against the Inners for a lifetime of oppression and injustice.

¬ª Watch the new season of The Expanse now exclusively with your Prime Membership: http://bit.ly/TheExpanseAPV
¬ª SUBSCRIBE: http://bit.ly/PrimeVideoSubscribe

About The Expanse:
The disappearance of rich-girl-turned-political-activist Julie Mao links the lives of Ceres detective Joe Miller (Thomas Jane), accidental ship captain James Holden (Steven Strait) and U.N. politician Chrisjen Avasarala (Shohreh Aghdashloo). Amidst political tension between Earth, Mars and the Belt, they unravel the single greatest conspiracy of all time.

About The Expanse Seasons 2:
In this noir thriller set two hundred years in the future, the case of a missing young woman leads a washed-up detective across the solar system to uncover the greatest conspiracy in human history.

About The Expanse Seasons 3:
As the Rocinante crew digs deeper into the search for Prax's missing daughter, the war between Earth and Mars turns deadly in ways the solar system has never seen. But a new threat in the outer reaches of the Belt could prove much more dangerous, threatening to test the very future of humanity.

About The Expanse Seasons 4:
Season 4 of The Expanse, its first as a global Amazon Original, begins a new chapter for the series with the crew of the Rocinante on a mission from the U.N. to explore new worlds beyond the Ring Gate. Humanity has been given access to thousands of Earth-like planets which has created a land rush and furthered tensions between the opposing nations of Earth, Mars and the Belt. Ilus is the first of these planets, one rich with natural resources but also marked by the ruins of a long dead alien civilization. While Earthers, Martians and Belters maneuver to colonize Ilus and its natural resources, these early explorers don‚Äôt understand this new world and are unaware of the larger dangers that await them.

snippet.title: Google Pixel 5 | Unboxing & Full Tour
snippet.description:
Unboxing Google's Pixel 5 flagship phone, plus a tour of the dual lens camera, Snapdragon 765G performance and best Android 11 features. My full review will hit in a couple of days but here's all you need to know about the specs and software - and let me know what you think of the Pixel 5 below.

This all-aluminium smartphone is the most premium Google handset of 2020, and a step up from the 4a and Pixel 4a 5G. You get a water resistant design for one, while the Gorilla Glass 5 finish should protect that 6-inch OLED display. That 90Hz refresh rate delivers a super smooth experience as you fly around Android, although the 'stereo' speakers aren't too hot.
 
Photo quality is on point from the 12.2MP main camera sensor, along with light portrait and nightscape mode smarts. You've also got a 16MP UWA lens on the Pixel 5, just like the 4a 5G. Gaming on PubG, Call of Duty and other Android titles isn't a problem courtesy of the 765G, which is also power efficient and boasts built-in 5G.

My review will test out the camera tech, gamer experience, battery life and other bits, and you can see my Pixel 5 vs 4a 5G vs 4a comparison soon to see how Google's smartphones all stack up.

snippet.title: Andrea Bocelli - You'll Never Walk Alone (Believe Studio Session)
snippet.description:
We are so proud to present this brand new recording of ‚ÄòYou‚Äôll Never Walk Alone‚Äô: an enduring message of unity and companionship. These themes run through the core of Andrea Bocelli‚Äôs brand new album, Believe, out 13th November 2020 and available to order now: https://AndreaBocelli.lnk.to/BelieveID

#Believe is a collection of uplifting songs that have inspired and sustained Andrea over the years, including a never before heard track from Maestro Ennio Morricone.

Follow Andrea Bocelli on:
Facebook - https://www.facebook.com/AndreaBocelli
Instagram - https://www.instagram.com/AndreaBocelli
Twitter - https://twitter.com/AndreaBocelli/
YouTube - https://www.youtube.com/AndreaBocelli

YOU WILL NEVER WALK ALONE
This hugely successful song is imbued with an innate charisma that elevates it to a composition that unites and warms the hearts of huge crowds. A kind of declaration of love and collective solidarity, this track reassures us that a ‚Äúgolden sky‚Äù awaits us after the storm. It was penned by the New York playwright Oscar Hammerstein (1895 ‚Äì 1960) and the composer Richard Rodgers (1902 ‚Äì 1979) for the musical ‚ÄúCarousel‚Äù which made its debut on Broadway in 1945. Due to the story of the musical that is inextricably linked to the song, in the United States it soon became a standard song sung at graduations. In the years that followed, it also arrived in the United Kingdom, with the Liverpudlian group ‚ÄúGerry and The Pacemakers‚Äù recording a cover of the song in 1963. However, many other famous voices have also tackled this enthralling melody, which would also go on to become one of the most beloved songs in the history of soccer.

snippet.title: EVERY DAY IMPOSTOR LIFE - AMONG US ANIMATION
snippet.description:
This time we want to show you how a impostor rejects to continue this way, and wants to help the crew, but at a certain moments the other members notice is a impostor, if he is good now, how can resolve this situation?
Thanks you so much for support me! 
I love you! ‚ù§Ô∏è

Original Animation by Hornstromp.

Among Us is an American made science fiction based murder mystery video game developed and published by Innersloth. Inc. It was released for IOS and Android on June 15, 2018, for PC on Steam on August 18, 2018 and for Dajolg on November 2, 2018. Among Us follows a crew being picked off one by one by an impostor.

In each game the player is one of 4 to 10 living and working in several different environments. One of these crewmates is an Impostor whose main goal is to kill everyone else. The remainder of the players are part of the regular crew who are just trying to escape unharmed. To do this, they have to complete several tasks or (better yet) find the Impostor and vote them out Survivor-style. If they are successful, the Crew wins. If the Impostor manages to kill them all, the player is victorious. In a 10 player game with one Impostor, there is a 10% chance of being an Impostor.

The free map, Skeld, has 14 different rooms that are connected by 7 hallways. Everyone begins the game in the Cafeteria and, depending on the host's settings, as well as on RNG, Crew members have to visit some or most of the other rooms to complete their tasks.

While Impostors do not have tasks as their specific objectives, they can fake ‚Äúcompleting‚Äù certain activities as a way to gain everyone else's trust. Every user has a chance to call an emergency meeting or, upon seeing a dead body, to report it to everyone else. For the mobile release, discussions are only possible during these time-limited events.

If you are an Impostor, your main goal is to convince others that you are not the Impostor, while the Crew's job is to spot you out. Since it is a voting system where the person with the most votes gets eliminated from the game, it does not really matter who does what. Instead, your argumentative powers are what makes a difference. To sway people in one direction or another, you have to be prepared to make your case as convincing as possible. There is a short time-limit, so you either have to present very strong evidence or come up with a believable narrative that will take others off your trail.

When you are killed by the Impostor, you become a ghost. Although you cannot interact or discuss with others, you can help them complete tasks.

Streamers complained about chat being main form of communications, so a lot of streamers used discord for voice chat.

Thanks you so much for support me! 
I love you! ‚ù§Ô∏è

Original Animation by Hornstromp.

Among Us is an American made science fiction based murder mystery video game developed and published by Innersloth. Inc. It was released for IOS and Android on June 15, 2018, for PC on Steam on August 18, 2018 and for Dajolg on November 2, 2018. Among Us follows a crew being picked off one by one by an impostor.

In each game the player is one of 4 to 10 living and working in several different environments. One of these crewmates is an Impostor whose main goal is to kill everyone else. The remainder of the players are part of the regular crew who are just trying to escape unharmed. To do this, they have to complete several tasks or (better yet) find the Impostor and vote them out Survivor-style. If they are successful, the Crew wins. If the Impostor manages to kill them all, the player is victorious. In a 10 player game with one Impostor, there is a 10% chance of being an Impostor.

The free map, Skeld, has 14 different rooms that are connected by 7 hallways. Everyone begins the game in the Cafeteria and, depending on the host's settings, as well as on RNG, Crew members have to visit some or most of the other rooms to complete their tasks.

While Impostors do not have tasks as their specific objectives, they can fake ‚Äúcompleting‚Äù certain activities as a way to gain everyone else's trust. Every user has a chance to call an emergency meeting or, upon seeing a dead body, to report it to everyone else. For the mobile release, discussions are only possible during these time-limited events.

If you are an Impostor, your main goal is to convince others that you are not the Impostor, while the Crew's job is to spot you out. Since it is a voting system where the person with the most votes gets eliminated from the game, it does not really matter who does what. Instead, your argumentative powers are what makes a difference. To sway people in one direction or another, you have to be prepared to make your case as convincing as possible. There is a short time-limit, so you either have to present very strong evidence or come up with a believable narrative that will take others off your trail.

When you are killed by the Impostor, you become a ghost. Although you cannot interact or discuss with others, you can help them complete tasks.

snippet.title: I Tested Clickbait DIY Soap "Hacks"
snippet.description:
Hello friends! So, after a long break from testing out & reviewing clickbait hack videos (I think the photo and video hacks broke me), we decided to make a comeback into the genre by testing out these viral clickbait soap hacks that lots of hackers seem to love making - from Blossom to 5-Minute Crafts to Craft Factory and back. And you know me, I can't resist me some nice soap :). We tried a cloud soap hack, a gummy bear soap hack, and a cinnamon roll soap hack, and shenanigans ensued. 

What do you guys think of these soap hacks??

Also, a heads up - though we mention it in the video - cinnamon can be dangerous to use on your skin and ivory soap can release fumes when being microwaved (I guess that's why it smelled so bad), so definitely be careful if you take on any of these soap art "hacks" yourself!!

You can check out Katie from Royalty Soap's video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-UDhSQYVWss
You can check out the Blossom video that contains our hacks here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4I1tMz-VMtg
And you can check out Jenna's soap hand video here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fo3HwJNgi9M

This video is NOT sponsored!!

Safiya's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/safiyany/

MUSIC
Via AudioNetwork

snippet.title: EVERTON 4-2 BRIGHTON | JAMES RODRIGUEZ AT THE DOUBLE! | PREMIER LEAGUE HIGHLIGHTS
snippet.description:
Everton continued their perfect start to the season with a 4-2 win over Brighton & Hove Albion - making it four Premier League wins from four and seven successive victories in all competitions. Goals from Dominic Calvert-Lewin, Terry Mina and James Rodriguez (2) gave Carlo Ancelotti's Blues all three points to take them back to the top of the table.

snippet.title: Donald Trump Is Back Home with COVID-19
snippet.description:
James Corden kicks off the show and dives right into the story that captured the world all weekend: The President of the United States has COVID-19 and was sent to Walter Reed Medical Center, and returned back to the White House. And nobody really seems to know what is going on, including his doctor.

Instagram: http://bit.ly/latelategram

Get new episodes of shows you love across devices the next day, stream live TV, and watch full seasons of CBS fan favorites anytime, anywhere with CBS All Access. Try it free! http://bit.ly/1OQA29B

Each week night, THE LATE LATE SHOW with JAMES CORDEN throws the ultimate late night after party with a mix of celebrity guests, edgy musical acts, games and sketches. Corden differentiates his show by offering viewers a peek behind-the-scenes into the green room, bringing all of his guests out at once and lending his musical and acting talents to various sketches. Additionally, bandleader Reggie Watts and the house band provide original, improvised music throughout the show. Since Corden took the reigns as host in March 2015, he has quickly become known for generating buzzworthy viral videos, such as Carpool Karaoke."

snippet.title: Telling My Family About My Mental Health Condition
snippet.description:
We asked four people about their mental health and family relationships. What they didn't know is that their family members were listening in.

If you are struggling with your mental health, please remember that support is always there if you need it. Speak out, ask for help from your loved ones or mental health professionals, or find out more about resources and services related to mental health on Belle, Beyond the Label helpbot https://go.gov.sg/belle-helpbot.

#beyondthelabel #togetheragainststigma #mentalhealthawareness #youarenotalone

00:00 - Introduction
00:45 - What would you say has been your biggest source of worry or stress? 
02:15 - Tell me more about the kind of worries or stress your face because of this.
04:15 - How have you been coping with these struggles?
06:31 - Who are you closest to in your family?
07:53 - What was it like growing up with your family member? 
09:28 - The Reveal
10:00 - What has he/she told you about their mental health 
12:25 - What happened when they tried to open up about their mental health to you? 
14:03 - What do you do to help each other feel supported at home?

snippet.title: Joe Biden and Donald Trump's fiery first debate‚ÄîHere are the highlights
snippet.description:
President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden got heated during their first chance to challenge each other face to face during the first presidential debate. Hardly a minute went by without one of the candidates interrupting the other, whether on the coronavirus, the Supreme Court or the economy. Even the moderator, Fox News' Chris Wallace, couldn't always stay above the fray. For access to live and exclusive video from CNBC subscribe to CNBC PRO: https://cnb.cx/2NGeIvi 

President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden had their first chance to challenge each other face to face. They did ‚Äî a lot.

Hardly a minute went by in the 90-minute brawl without one of the candidates angrily interrupting the other, whether on the coronavirus pandemic, the Supreme Court, the economy or anything else, including each other‚Äôs families.

‚ÄúWill you shut up, man?‚Äù Biden snapped at Trump at one point. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre the worst president America has ever had,‚Äù he said later.

‚ÄúChina ate your lunch,‚Äù Trump shot back at Biden during questions on the economy.

Even the moderator, Fox News‚Äô Chris Wallace, couldn‚Äôt always stay above the fray.

‚ÄúI hate to raise my voice, but why shouldn‚Äôt I be different than the two of you?‚Äù the exasperated host said at one point.

Here are the highlights.

snippet.title: I Tested Clickbait DIY Soap "Hacks"
snippet.description:
Hello friends! So, after a long break from testing out & reviewing clickbait hack videos (I think the photo and video hacks broke me), we decided to make a comeback into the genre by testing out these viral clickbait soap hacks that lots of hackers seem to love making - from Blossom to 5-Minute Crafts to Craft Factory and back. And you know me, I can't resist me some nice soap :). We tried a cloud soap hack, a gummy bear soap hack, and a cinnamon roll soap hack, and shenanigans ensued. 

What do you guys think of these soap hacks??

Also, a heads up - though we mention it in the video - cinnamon can be dangerous to use on your skin and ivory soap can release fumes when being microwaved (I guess that's why it smelled so bad), so definitely be careful if you take on any of these soap art "hacks" yourself!!

You can check out Katie from Royalty Soap's video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-UDhSQYVWss
You can check out the Blossom video that contains our hacks here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4I1tMz-VMtg
And you can check out Jenna's soap hand video here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fo3HwJNgi9M

This video is NOT sponsored!!

Safiya's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/safiyany/

MUSIC
Via AudioNetwork

snippet.title: HIGHLIGHTS | Liverpool vs Arsenal (3-1) | Premier League
snippet.description:
Our winning start to the season is over after Liverpool fought back to beat us at Anfield.
 
A bizarre goal from Alex Lacazette saw us lead the champions and lay the foundations for a memorable result. But our advantage lasted just two minutes as Sadio Mane and Andy Robertson struck to turn the tide in Liverpool's favour.

Diogo Jota then put the game to bed moments before full time with a crisp finish into the bottom left-hand corner. 

#arsenal #highlights #premierleague

For more match action, highlights and training videos, make sure you become a digital member and sign up to Arsenal Player. It's FREE and is the Home of the Game: https://arsn.al/arsenalplayer

This is the Official YouTube channel for Arsenal Football Club. This channel will aim to showcase the personality of Arsenal Football Club and give fans more of an insight into what it's like to be at this fantastic club. This channel will look behind the scenes and get closer to the likes of Mesut Ozil, Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang, David Luiz, Nicolas Pepe, Alexandre Lacazette, Mesut Ozil, Bernd Leno, Granit Xhaka, Hector Bellerin, Bukayo Saka, Gabriel Martinelli, Bukayo and more.

ABOUT ARSENAL FC


Arsenal Football Club were formed in 1886. They have amassed 13 League titles, 14 FA Cups and many other major trophies since then. Their greatest players include: Thierry Henry, Dennis Bergkamp, Tony Adams, Ian Wright, Robert Pires, Liam Brady, Patrick Vieira, Cliff Bastin and Charlie George.

Highlights (if you can call them that) from the first US Presidential debate between Donald Trump and Joe Biden in Ohio.

snippet.title: I Tested Clickbait DIY Soap "Hacks"
snippet.description:
Hello friends! So, after a long break from testing out & reviewing clickbait hack videos (I think the photo and video hacks broke me), we decided to make a comeback into the genre by testing out these viral clickbait soap hacks that lots of hackers seem to love making - from Blossom to 5-Minute Crafts to Craft Factory and back. And you know me, I can't resist me some nice soap :). We tried a cloud soap hack, a gummy bear soap hack, and a cinnamon roll soap hack, and shenanigans ensued. 

What do you guys think of these soap hacks??

Also, a heads up - though we mention it in the video - cinnamon can be dangerous to use on your skin and ivory soap can release fumes when being microwaved (I guess that's why it smelled so bad), so definitely be careful if you take on any of these soap art "hacks" yourself!!

You can check out Katie from Royalty Soap's video here: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-UDhSQYVWss
You can check out the Blossom video that contains our hacks here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4I1tMz-VMtg
And you can check out Jenna's soap hand video here:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Fo3HwJNgi9M

This video is NOT sponsored!!

Safiya's Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/safiyany/

MUSIC
Via AudioNetwork

snippet.title: Cape York | FLOODED 4WDs & the world‚Äôs best campsites | Budget build HiLux takes on the rest!
snippet.description:
Shauno & Jocko are back to take on the Old Telegraph Track in Cape York! Is there ANY better place to run in the 30?! Driving some of the best 4WD tracks in Australia the Dirty 30 and Pony Lux tackle the Tele Track, Gunshot Creek, Nolan's Brook, Palm Creek, Cockatoo Creek, Sam's Creek, Eliot Falls... the whole lot!

Wanna get the same Snatch Gear Shauno and Jock wear? Head to: https://snatchclothing.com.au/

Shauno's running the tough as nails Goodyear Wrangler Duratrac ATs - learn more: https://www.goodyear.com.au/

Sparesbox is the home of spares and accessories: https://www.sparesbox.com.au/

Check out Drifta roof top tents here: https://www.drifta.com.au/

Get the same suspension Shauno trusts in the Dirty 30: https://fulcrumsuspensions.com.au/

Shauno is running Teralume Icon driving lights - find them here: https://www.teralumeindustries.com/

Shaun & Graham rely on Nebo head torches and spotlights at night at camp - you can find them here: https://nebotools.com.au/

Shaun trusts Castrol oils in all his 4WDs. Learn More: https://rego2oil.castrol.com/en_au/au...

snippet.title: Joe Biden and Donald Trump's fiery first debate‚ÄîHere are the highlights
snippet.description:
President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden got heated during their first chance to challenge each other face to face during the first presidential debate. Hardly a minute went by without one of the candidates interrupting the other, whether on the coronavirus, the Supreme Court or the economy. Even the moderator, Fox News' Chris Wallace, couldn't always stay above the fray. For access to live and exclusive video from CNBC subscribe to CNBC PRO: https://cnb.cx/2NGeIvi 

President Donald Trump and former Vice President Joe Biden had their first chance to challenge each other face to face. They did ‚Äî a lot.

Hardly a minute went by in the 90-minute brawl without one of the candidates angrily interrupting the other, whether on the coronavirus pandemic, the Supreme Court, the economy or anything else, including each other‚Äôs families.

‚ÄúWill you shut up, man?‚Äù Biden snapped at Trump at one point. ‚ÄúYou‚Äôre the worst president America has ever had,‚Äù he said later.

‚ÄúChina ate your lunch,‚Äù Trump shot back at Biden during questions on the economy.

Even the moderator, Fox News‚Äô Chris Wallace, couldn‚Äôt always stay above the fray.

‚ÄúI hate to raise my voice, but why shouldn‚Äôt I be different than the two of you?‚Äù the exasperated host said at one point.

Here are the highlights.

snippet.title: Here‚Äôs Why Trump‚Äôs COVID Diagnosis Was A Disaster
snippet.description: President Trump was diagnosed with COVID-19. Even though it‚Äôs been several days now, and we‚Äôve known this was possible for months, it‚Äôs still so bizarre to read. Unfortunately, the tragedy of COVID-19 does not just stop at the infection of people like Donald Trump, but rather extends to the megaphones of our most mainstream media outlets. I‚Äôve been in more Twitter feuds over the last week than I have been in my entire life on the platform, arguing with contributors to outlets like CNN, The Washington Post, and Fox News, among others. It seems to me that this virus and our political vitriol towards each other has caused us to lose all sense of logic and decency. From criticizing DO‚Äôs (Doctor‚Äôs of Osteopathic Medicine) for being inferior to asking doctors on TV to participate in ‚Äútabloid medicine‚Äù, I‚Äôm almost beginning to lose my cool. Today I walk you through what‚Äôs brought me to my breaking point.

snippet.title: The Infinite Pattern That Never Repeats
snippet.description:
Simples rules of geometry meant that 5-fold symmetry was impossible as were crystals without a periodic structure. This turns out to be wrong. Thanks to LastPass for sponsoring a portion of this video. Click here to start using LastPass: https://ve42.co/LPs

Huge thanks to Prof. Paul Steinhardt for the interview on this topic. Check out his book ‚ÄòThe Second Kind of Impossible‚Äô

If you'd like to learn more about Penrose tilings, go check out "Penrose Tiles to Trapdoor Ciphers" by Martin Gardener, which helped my research for this video.

Filmed by Gene Nagata (Potato Jet on YouTube)
Animations by Iv√°n Tello and Jonny Hyman
Editing, Coloring, Music & Audio mastering by Jonny Hyman

Prague scenes filmed in 2012.
Special thanks to Raquel Nuno for helping with the tilings!

Hi guys!! Here's a little something we've been working on since earlier last year... I don't like to brag, but I promise ya this smells delicious!!

snippet.title: President Trump and Melania Trump test positive for Covid-19
snippet.description:
President Donald Trump and first lady Melania Trump tested positive for coronavirus, the President announced early Friday morning, an extraordinary development coming months into a global pandemic and in the final stretch of his reelection campaign.
"Tonight, @FLOTUS and I tested positive for COVID-19. We will begin our quarantine and recovery process immediately. We will get through this TOGETHER!" Trump tweeted shortly before 1 am Friday.
In a memo issued to reporters around 1 a.m. ET, the President's physician, Navy Commander Dr. Sean Conley, wrote he received confirmation of the positive tests on Thursday evening.
"The President and First Lady are both well at this time, and they plan to remain at home within the White House during their convalescence," Conley wrote.

#Covid #Trump #CNN #News

snippet.title: Israel Adesanya's Coach: Paulo Costa Win, Jon Jones Twitter Beef, Jan Blachowicz, Weidman, Chimaev
snippet.description:
In the aftermath of UFC 253: Adesanya vs. Costa, Israel Adesanya, City Kickboxing head coach Eugene Bareman speaks to Submission Radio about Israel's masterclass win over Paulo Costa, what's next for Israel and if he could realistically fight again in 2020, if the Jan Blachowicz fight could be a possibility, Israel's pec controversy, the recent Twitter exchange between Jon Jones and Israel Adesanya and why Eugene doesn't approve, what would have to happen in order for that fight to come together, Shane Young's opponent missing weight and why Eugene considers it the same as cheating, the punch mistaken for an eye poke in Brad Riddell's fight, and more!

0:00 Intro
1:20 How he grades Israel's performance over Costa
2:38 Paulo Costa's gameplan in the fight
3:58 What the gameplan was
5:56 If Israel's opponents are starting to get beaten ahead of the fight
8:20 The moment Eugene knew the fight was over and in the bag
9:30 The controversy surrounding Israel's pec
11:00 Why Israel has never taken any steroids
12:14 If there are any updates on Israel's chest
13:18 Israel saying he wants to fight again in 2020 and who it could be against
14:50 If Jan Blachowicz could be an option for the light heavyweight belt
17:20 Chris Weidman as an opponent
19:26 Khamzat Chimaev
21:10 The Jon Jones/Adesanya Twitter war and why Eugene doesn't approve
24:30 If Jones is trying to capitalize before his heavyweight move
26:25 What would have to happen in order for Jones/Adesanya to happen
28:35 Why Eugene considers fighters missing weight as cheating
34:15 How Eugene's handled his own fighter missing weight
35:31 The punch mistaken for an eye poke in Brad Riddell's fight

As perguntas t√™m quatro n√≠veis de dificuldade: f√°cil, m√©dio, dif√≠cil e a Pergunta do Milhonze (que ter√° seu tema sorteado em uma roleta no final do programa).

Jetzt streamen: https://www.tvnow.de/shows/pocher-gefaehrlich-ehrlich-18585?utm_source=youtube&utm_medium=editorial&utm_campaign=beschreibung&utm_term=rtl

Nach Michael Wendlers freiwilligem Ausstieg bei DSDS und seinen wirren Aussagen bei Instagram ist sein Manager Markus Krampe (44) live zu Gast bei Oliver Pocher in der Late-Night "Pocher ‚Äì gef√§hrlich ehrlich!". Seine Konsequenz aus dem Ganzen: Ab sofort gehen Manager und S√§nger wohl getrennte Wege. Markus Krampe kennt den Wendler und ist zutiefst entsetzt √ºber sein Verhalten: "Ich bin geschockt". Markus Krampe sagt aber auch: "Das hat sich angedeutet". Warum, erkl√§rt er ausf√ºhrlich im Video.

"F√ºr mich ist er krank", sagt Markus Krampe. Kurz vor seinem Instagram-Post hat Michael Wendler ihn im Auto angerufen und gesagt: "Wir werden alle sterben!" Krampe ist sich sicher: Michael Wendlers "Karriere ist beendet". Der Kaufland-Werbe-Deal ist bereits geplatzt, die Supermarktkette hat sich bei Twitter von Wendler distanziert und den Werbeclip runtergenommen. Der Schlager-Star habe schon seit l√§ngerem mit Verschw√∂rungstheorien in Sachen Corona sympathisiert. Wie konkret, erkl√§rt Markus Krampe oben im Video. 

Eine weitere Zusammenarbeit mit dem Wendler sieht Markus Krampe kritisch: "Es ist klar, dass wir nicht mehr zusammenarbeiten werden ‚Ä¶ Ich will, dass er sich professionelle Hilfe sucht." Michaels abstruses Verhalten habe wohl mit seiner Vergangenheit zu tun, wie er im Video berichtet.

Auch RTL hat sich bereits deutlich von Michael Wendlers Aussagen distanziert.

Da stehen selbst einem hartgesottenen PR-Profi wie Markus Krampe Tr√§nen in den Augen. Der Manager von Michael Wendler muss sich im Gespr√§ch mit Olli Pocher (42) in dessen Latenight-Show "Pocher ‚Äì gef√§hrlich ehrlich" zusammenrei√üen. Wendler erregte am Donnerstag Riesenaufsehen, indem er seinen Jury-Job in der DSDS-Jury k√ºndigte und seine Entscheidung mit verschw√∂rungstheoretischen Begr√ºndungen erkl√§rte. Krampe hatte schon in den letzten Tagen ein ungutes Gef√ºhl bei Wendlers Verhalten. Im Video erkl√§rt er, welche Rolle Laura in dem ganzen Wendler-Wahnsinn einnimmt.

"Also die Laura ist Tag und Nacht mit ihm zusammen und sie h√∂rt sich das alles an. Michael Wendler hat ein sehr einnehmendes Wesen, er kann Leute mitrei√üen", so Markus Krampe. "Ich glaube nicht, dass sie vieles so teilt wie er. Aber nat√ºrlich sind die ein Paar, sie sind verheiratet. Die lieben sich wirklich, die sind ein echtes Paar."

W√§hrend Michael Wendler auf Instagram seinen DSDS-R√ºcktritt und wirre Verschw√∂rungsaussagen verk√ºndet, k√ºmmert sich Laura um Halloween-Deko im Haus in Florida.

Eine absurde Situation, denn in Deutschland drohen diverse Medien- und Marketingvertr√§ge zugrunde zu gehen. Gerade erst wurde ein Werbespot von Wendler und Laura mit einer gro√üen Supermarkt-Kette ver√∂ffentlicht, schon ist er wieder gel√∂scht worden. Der Grund: Der H√§ndler distanziert sich klar von Wendlers Aussagen.

Markus Krampe hat am Donnerstag noch mit Laura geschrieben. "Sie ist sich der Sache nicht bewusst. Sie hat mich gefragt, warum der Kaufland-Spot gel√∂scht ist", so Krampe.

snippet.title: Corona hat meine Meinung ge√§ndert
snippet.description:
Vor Corona war ich der festen √úberzeugung: Wir brauchen mehr Wissenschaftlerinnen und Wissenschaftler in den Medien - f√ºr mehr wissenschaftliche Aufkl√§rung!
Doch so wie es momentan l√§uft, sorgen mehr Wissenschaftler in den Medien nur f√ºr mehr Verwirrung. Was wir zuerst brauchen, ist eine Qualit√§tskontrolle der Wissenschaftskommunikation.

INHALT
0:00 Corona hat meine Meinung ge√§ndert
0:53 Wissenschaft kann man trauen, Wissenschaftlern nicht
6:02 Kann man maiLab trauen??
7:29 Warum Experten nicht immer richtig liegen
10:11 Das Bhakdi-Ph√§nomen: Gro√üe B√ºhne f√ºr Schwarze Schafe
13:53 Vertrauen ist gut, Kontrolle ist besser
15:39 Bundesverdienstkreuz waaaaaas

‚ñ∫ Hier geht‚Äôs zu meinem Gespr√§ch mit dem Bundespr√§sidenten: https://www.facebook.com/431035763934153/posts/1241970619507326/
oder hier: https://www.instagram.com/tv/CGEozmQqc_2/?igshid=vtc8qrtb72bu
 
***Gl√ºckwunsch an die anderen Ordenstr√§gerInnen*** https://bit.ly/36JBrl4


WEITERE INFOS & QUELLEN

Leitlinien f√ºr gute Wissenschafts-PR: https://www.wissenschaft-im-dialog.de/blog/blogartikel/beitrag/finale-version-der-leitlinien-zur-guten-wissenschafts-pr-veroeffentlicht/

Video zu Methoden in klinischen Studien (Randomisierte, kontrollierte Studien, Verblindung, uvm.) - Kann Handystrahlung Krebs ausl√∂sen?: https://youtu.be/1AJBcyI_u0U

Video zu statistischen Methoden - Wie wir uns mit Zahlen manipulieren lassen: https://youtu.be/M0VpTjZL57U 

Corona-Langzeitsch√§den? Quarks Corona in 5 Minuten: https://www1.wdr.de/mediathek/video/sendungen/quarks-corona-in-fuenf-minuten/video-welche-langzeitfolgen-gibt-es-100.html

NERD-TIPP: Peer Review und sog. Predatory Journals, ‚ÄúRaubjournalen‚Äù, die jeden Mist als ‚Äúwissenschaftliche Studie‚Äù ver√∂ffentlichen - Der Betrug an der Wissenschaft: https://youtu.be/qKQeJM2tZJc

Ein konkretes Beispiel f√ºr offenen, kritischen Diskurs zwischen Expert/innen, hatten wir bei dem Thema ‚ÄúGibt es m√§nnlcihe und weibliche Gehirne?‚Äù - hier das Video (siehe auch Videobeschreibung f√ºr die entsprechenden Quellen, unter dem Abschnitt *verschieden vernetzt*): https://youtu.be/xt2Bgkqk71I 

Konkretes Beispiel f√ºr einen zwar ver√∂ffentlichten Artikel, der aber wieder zur√ºckgezogen wurde (passend zu Kary Mullis und die AIDS-Leugnung, s.u.) - der ‚Äúsachliche Backlash‚Äù ist auf derselben Seite verlinkt: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC4172096/ 

Thomas Edison grausame Demonstrationen an streunenden Tieren, um seine Rivalen Westinghouse und Tesla (Team Wechselstrom) zu diskreditieren: https://bit.ly/2SED9vu 
(im Text steht √ºbrigens auch, dass Edison einen Elefanten mit Strom get√∂tet habe. Allerdings ist das h√∂chstwahrscheinlich nur ein Mythos, wie in einem anderen Artikel vom Smithsonian Magazine ebenfalls berichtet wird: https://bit.ly/3dafz3b) 

Medizinnobelpreistr√§ger James Watson und seine menschenfeindlichen Statements: 
https://liorpachter.wordpress.com/2018/05/18/james-watson-in-his-own-words/ 
(hier bitte nicht nur Zitate ohne Kontext lesen; jedes Zitat ist mit einem Hyperlink versehen, was euch zur Quelle bringt)

√úber Chemienobelpreistr√§ger Linus Pauling und seine Fehleinsch√§tzung von Vitamin C, die sich bis heute noch hartn√§ckig h√§lt (Quellen in der Videobeschreibung): https://youtu.be/H9GY49bsp9o

Dieser NYT Artikel beschreibst sowohl Watson als auch Kary Mullis, der u.a. AIDS leugnet, ‚ÄúBright Minds, dim Notions‚Äù: https://nyti.ms/3jEizHC

Doch so wie es momentan l√§uft, sorgen mehr Wissenschaftler in den Medien nur f√ºr mehr Verwirrung. Was wir zuerst brauchen, ist eine Qualit√§tskontrolle der Wissenschaftskommunikation.

Ob Ari das trotz ihrer H√∂henangst gelingen wird oder ob ihr in luftiger H√∂he spei√ºbel wird, seht ihr in dieser ‚ÄûDas schaffst du nie!‚Äú-Challenge.

Trotz Sonnenschein und bester Aussicht √ºber den M√ºnchner Olympiapark hat Ari aber keine Zeit ihre Fahrten im Kettenkarussell zu genie√üen. W√§hrenddessen m√ºssen n√§mlich drei Geschicklichkeitsspiele bew√§ltigt werden. Gef√§hrlich! ABER, Spoiler: Immerhin ist auch Gaffa am Start!

Und zwar den Bayern-Tower, der sonst auf dem M√ºnchner Oktoberfest steht. Wind, H√∂henangst, Fliehkraft: Mit jedem Meter H√∂he werden die Geschicklichkeitsspiele f√ºr Ari schwerer. snippet.title: KAISERSCHMARRNDRAMA - offizieller Trailer
snippet.description:
Kinostart: 12. November 2020
Die Idylle des niederbayerischen Provinzpolizisten Franz Eberhofer (Sebastian Bezzel) ist in Gefahr. Das liegt weniger daran, dass das dorfbekannte Webcam-Girl ermordet wurde ‚Äì diesen Fall geht der Franz mit der gewohnten Tiefenentspanntheit an. Ausgerechnet jetzt sitzt sein aufdringlicher, aber stets hilfreicher Co-Ermittler Rudi (Simon Schwarz) nach einem Unfall im Rollstuhl und gibt nat√ºrlich Franz die Schuld daf√ºr. Als Rudi sich dann auch noch auf dem Hof einnistet und eine Rundumbetreuung von Franz erwartet, ziehen erste dunkle Wolken im Paradies auf. Richtig bedroht wird Eberhofers Ruhe aber durch Dauerfreundin Susi (Lisa-Maria Potthoff), die sich mit Franz‚Äò verhasstem Bruder Leopold (Gerhard Wittmann) verb√ºndet hat, um neben dem Hof ein Doppelfamilienhaus mit Gemeinschaftssauna zu bauen - was auch Papa Eberhofer geh√∂rig gegen den Strich geht. Und als w√§re das Dorfleben mit einer rebellischen Motorradgang und Marihuana-Fleischpflanzerln nicht schon bunt genug, muss Franz auch noch entdecken, dass seine Freunde Simmerl (Stephan Zinner) und Fl√∂tzinger (Daniel Christensen) Stammkunden beim Mordopfer waren.

snippet.title: EVERY DAY IMPOSTOR LIFE - AMONG US ANIMATION
snippet.description:
This time we want to show you how a impostor rejects to continue this way, and wants to help the crew, but at a certain moments the other members notice is a impostor, if he is good now, how can resolve this situation?
Thanks you so much for support me! 
I love you! ‚ù§Ô∏è

Original Animation by Hornstromp.

Among Us is an American made science fiction based murder mystery video game developed and published by Innersloth. Inc. It was released for IOS and Android on June 15, 2018, for PC on Steam on August 18, 2018 and for Dajolg on November 2, 2018. Among Us follows a crew being picked off one by one by an impostor.

In each game the player is one of 4 to 10 living and working in several different environments. One of these crewmates is an Impostor whose main goal is to kill everyone else. The remainder of the players are part of the regular crew who are just trying to escape unharmed. To do this, they have to complete several tasks or (better yet) find the Impostor and vote them out Survivor-style. If they are successful, the Crew wins. If the Impostor manages to kill them all, the player is victorious. In a 10 player game with one Impostor, there is a 10% chance of being an Impostor.

The free map, Skeld, has 14 different rooms that are connected by 7 hallways. Everyone begins the game in the Cafeteria and, depending on the host's settings, as well as on RNG, Crew members have to visit some or most of the other rooms to complete their tasks.

While Impostors do not have tasks as their specific objectives, they can fake ‚Äúcompleting‚Äù certain activities as a way to gain everyone else's trust. Every user has a chance to call an emergency meeting or, upon seeing a dead body, to report it to everyone else. For the mobile release, discussions are only possible during these time-limited events.

If you are an Impostor, your main goal is to convince others that you are not the Impostor, while the Crew's job is to spot you out. Since it is a voting system where the person with the most votes gets eliminated from the game, it does not really matter who does what. Instead, your argumentative powers are what makes a difference. To sway people in one direction or another, you have to be prepared to make your case as convincing as possible. There is a short time-limit, so you either have to present very strong evidence or come up with a believable narrative that will take others off your trail.

When you are killed by the Impostor, you become a ghost. Although you cannot interact or discuss with others, you can help them complete tasks.

Streamers complained about chat being main form of communications, so a lot of streamers used discord for voice chat.

#AmongUs #AmongUsMeme
#AmongUsAnimation

Among Us‚Äã es un videojuego modo fiesta multijugador en l√≠nea desarrollado por InnerSloth y lanzado el 15 de junio de 2018. El juego tiene un grupo de jugadores a bordo de una nave espacial, cada uno de los cuales asume uno de los dos roles, la mayor√≠a son compa√±eros de tripulaci√≥n y algunos son impostores.

En esta ocasi√≥n queremos mostrarte a un impostor que rechaza seguir  as√≠, y quiere ayudar a la tripulaci√≥n, pero en un determinado momento los dem√°s miembros notan que es un impostor, si es bueno ahora, ¬øc√≥mo se puede resolver esta situaci√≥n?

Animaci√≥n original de Hornstromp.

Among Us es un videojuego de misterio de asesinatos basado en ciencia ficci√≥n, desarrollado y publicado por Innersloth. Inc. Fue lanzado para IOS y Android el 15 de junio de 2018, para PC en Steam el 18 de agosto de 2018 y para Dajolg el 2 de noviembre de 2018. Among Us sigue a un equipo que fue recogido uno por uno por un impostor.

En cada juego, el jugador es uno de los 4 a 10 que viven y trabajan en varios entornos diferentes. Uno de estos compa√±eros de tripulaci√≥n es un impostor cuyo objetivo principal es matar a todos los dem√°s. El resto de los jugadores son parte de la tripulaci√≥n regular que solo est√°n tratando de escapar ilesos. Para hacer esto, tienen que completar varias tareas o (mejor a√∫n) encontrar al Impostor y rechazarlo al estilo Survivor. Si tienen √©xito, la Tripulaci√≥n gana. Si el Impostor logra matarlos a todos, el jugador sale victorioso. En un juego de 10 jugadores con un impostor, hay un 10% de posibilidades de ser un impostor.

El mapa gratuito, Skeld, tiene 14 habitaciones diferentes que est√°n conectadas por 7 pasillos. Todos comienzan el juego en la Cafeter√≠a y, dependiendo de la configuraci√≥n del anfitri√≥n, as√≠ como del RNG, los miembros de la tripulaci√≥n deben visitar algunas o la mayor√≠a de las otras salas para completar sus tareas.

Si bien los impostores no tienen tareas como objetivos espec√≠ficos, pueden fingir "completar" ciertas actividades como una forma de ganarse la confianza de los dem√°s. Cada usuario tiene la oportunidad de convocar una reuni√≥n de emergencia o, al ver un cad√°ver, informar a todos los dem√°s. Para el lanzamiento m√≥vil, las discusiones solo son posibles durante estos eventos de tiempo limitado.

Si eres un impostor, tu objetivo principal es convencer a los dem√°s de que no eres el impostor, mientras que el trabajo de la tripulaci√≥n es detectarlo. Dado que es un sistema de votaci√≥n donde la persona con m√°s votos es eliminada del juego, realmente no importa qui√©n haga qu√©. En cambio, sus poderes de argumentaci√≥n son los que marcan la diferencia. Para influir en la gente en una direcci√≥n u otra, debe estar preparado para que su caso sea lo m√°s convincente posible. Hay un l√≠mite de tiempo corto, por lo que debe presentar pruebas muy s√≥lidas o presentar una narrativa cre√≠ble que desv√≠e a otros de su camino.
